The paper deals with activity localization in videos, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in the sub-categories cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel representation for ranking proposals, which involves capturing context around a proposal, which could fall under the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with classification of activities, which could also fall under the sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language).
